A robotics startup captures attention with a small drone flying above its booth. Recruiters distribute tote bags filled with branded notebooks, pens, water bottles, and phone chargers. Event staff scan registrations and hand out lanyards at the entrance, while human resources teams note information on tablets as students introduce themselves. Students also use tablets at kiosks to upload resumes to the fair database. Career counselors assist students in navigating applicable industries, and international students queue for advice on visa sponsorship requirements. Friends decompress on the quad, comparing company responses and swag items. Alumni volunteers provide pep talks near the coffee station. Career center staff log attendance metrics on laptops as students exit with tote bags and business cards, while finance firms offer QR codes for immediate internship applications. The dean thanks recruiters for their support, as alumni discuss preparing for technical interviews.

Small groups of students assess which recruiters appear most enthusiastic, while others mark target employers on the event map. Career counselors assist unsure students in finding suitable industries, and career center staff track attendance with laptops. Students exit with tote bags and a collection of business cards, having uploaded their resumes to the fair database at kiosks using tablets. Recruiters encourage students to follow up with personalized emails. Meanwhile, volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures. Additionally, workshops on networking etiquette begin in the adjoining classroom.
